==Translingual==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} exceptio: an exception + bene facio - are: to do well hence a privilege + excutio - excutere: to throw off hence to reject + ordiniatio - onis: setting in order hence  regulating + sive - seu: if this then that.

===Phrase===
#(Law:) An [[exception]] whereby a debtor claims the benefit of [[excussion]].
[[Category: Law]]

